=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/CreativeWork\" ><div class='avia_textblock'  itemprop=\"text\" ><h2 class=\"title-default-left\">About COMPUDON Junior Championship<\/h2>\n<p><strong>The NITI Aayog Report titled &#8220;Strategy for New India @75&#8221; indicates that India needs to eliminate the Digital Divide by 2022-23 so there is lot of emphasis on spreading the key 21<sup>st<\/sup> century skill of 21<sup>st<\/sup> Century- the Digital Literacy.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>COMPUDON JUNIOR is a National Championship for junior School students inspired by Microsoft\u2019s Digital Literacy Standard, which teaches generic ICT skills and concepts. In addition, the championship curricula also covers additional content to help participants stay safe online and get an overview of new technologies.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This Digital Literacy Championship will test School students\u2019 generic ICT skills that are essential for students in the 21st Century. There are 2 levels of this school-focused championship and the top 400 high-scoring school students from around the country will be invited to compete in the India Finals round of this National Championship. In the India Finals, these school students will also be representing their school and their region and competing to WIN several awards. <strong>There are over 100 awards to be won which include awards such as India Champion, National Runners Up, Regional Awards, National Celebrated List Winners and National Merit List Winners (subject to minimum participation from participating schools) as well. The Winner will win the coveted title of India Champion.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">COMPUDON Junior is open to school students between the ages of 8-14 years (as on August 15, 2023).<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The championship aims at providing the digital literacy skills that are critical to succeed in the 21st century. Preparing for the championship will not only help school students acquire and master these skills but prepare them to thrive and take advantage of the opportunities being created in the 21st-century global economy. The practice exams provided will help students understand the type of questions, and the time available and prepare them to win the championship.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">COMPUDON JUNIOR is brought to you by CyberLearning Educational Society. which is also the organizer of COMPUDON (<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>WWW.COMPUDON.IN<\/strong><\/span>) \u2013 now amongst India\u2019s most popular student championships. COMPUDON is India\u2019s first ever Official Championship on MS Office Skills, which tests students\u2019 skill levels on MS Word, MS Excel &amp; MS PowerPoint through an online test that is based on real-time-hands on the skill-based exam.<\/p>\n<p><strong>COMPUDON India champions have won all top positions including the Covered Title of World Champion in PowerPoint, this was won by Arjit Kansal, student of Maharaja Agrasen Model School, Pitam Pura, New Delhi.<\/strong><\/p>\n<\/div><\/section>\n\n<style type=\"text\/css\" data-created_by=\"avia_inline_auto\" id=\"style-css-av-34j7p0-2b3e555fa39eaec9250a33136416ba88\">\n#top .av_textblock_section.av-34j7p0-2b3e555fa39eaec9250a33136416ba88 .avia_textblock{\nfont-size:14px;\n}\n<\/style>\n<section  class='av_textblock_section av-34j7p0-2b3e555fa39eaec9250a33136416ba88 '   itemscope=\"itemscope\" itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/CreativeWork\" ><div class='avia_textblock'  itemprop=\"text\" ><h2 class=\"title-default-left\"><\/h2>\n<h2 class=\"title-default-left\">About CyberLearning Educational Society (CES)<\/h2>\n<p>CES is a NGO arm of India CyberLearning Pvt Ltd., which is a Global Training Partner of Microsoft and is a group of committed individuals who are problem-solvers &amp; leaders, who want to create a lasting change and want to empower &amp; secure every child through digital literacy for success in 21<sup>st<\/sup> century global economy.<\/p>\n<p>For more than 15 years, CES has contributed to the cause of digital literacy through partnerships wth over 50 Rotary Clubs in Rotary International District 3010, which then got divided in to Districts 3011 &amp; 3012 and Times Foundation. CES has supported youth from minorities and under privileged sections in the form of training &amp; global certification scholarships worth 2 crores.<\/p>\n<p>CES is also the organizer of <a style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: Underline;\" href=\"http:\/\/WWW.COMPUDON.IN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WWW.COMPUDON.IN<\/a> &#8211; India\u2019s first ever-Official Championship on Microsoft Office Specialist Certifications and the National Championship on Digital Literacy- <a style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: Underline;\" href=\"http:\/\/WWW.COMPUDONJUNIOR.IN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WWW.COMPUDONJUNIOR.IN<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div><\/section>\n\n<style type=\"text\/css\" data-created_by=\"avia_inline_auto\" id=\"style-css-av-la457x25-d1041cddff08a07624cabd733c187764\">\n.avia-image-container.av-la457x25-d1041cddff08a07624cabd733c187764 img.avia_image{\nbox-shadow:none;\n}\n.avia-image-container.av-la457x25-d1041cddff08a07624cabd733c187764 .av-image-caption-overlay-center{\ncolor:#ffffff;\n}\n<\/style>\n<div  class='avia-image-container av-la457x25-d1041cddff08a07624cabd733c187764 av-styling- avia-align-center  avia-builder-el-5  el_after_av_textblock  avia-builder-el-last '   itemprop=\"image\" itemscope=\"itemscope\" itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/ImageObject\" ><div class=\"avia-image-container-inner\"><div class=\"avia-image-overlay-wrap\"><img decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" class='wp-image-4628 avia-img-lazy-loading-not-4628 avia_image ' src=\"https:\/\/compudonjunior.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/CES-1030x579.jpeg\" alt='' title='CES'  height=\"579\" width=\"1030\"  itemprop=\"thumbnailUrl\" srcset=\"https:\/\/compudonjunior.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2